{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"72663c7d-ed5c-40a1-bac1-a3f9dc7193fe","content":"This is a well-known MTP behavioral difference. **Exit code 8** means \"zero tests discovered,\" which MTP treats as an error by default (VSTest did not).\n\n**Fix:** Add the `--ignore-exit-code` option to tell MTP to return exit code 0 when no tests are found. In your `.csproj`, set:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--ignore-exit-code 8</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>\n```\n\nOr, in your CI pipeline's `dotnet test` invocation:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --ignore-exit-code 8\n```\n\nOr, set the environment variable:\n\n```\nTESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\n```\n\nLet me apply the project-level fix:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_BJb5RGd9hEB5GcMYNOKtRo","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1e83e43107be41c5b3afb7fad77b57ee/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--ignore-exit-code 8</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1e83e43107be41c5b3afb7fad77b57ee/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"b6fb8af5-8d65-4f66-96a9-55bcac803de1","outputTokens":514,"requestId":"E3C5:AB6AD:1C8373D:1F81784:6A052101"},"id":"43359d69-d728-4afa-8e24-0c1013945f67","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:10:36.288Z","parentId":"0073d8c7-71b3-4a0a-83e1-506b4a462eb4"}
